242. Valid Anagram
Solved
Easy
Topics
premium lock icon
Companies
Given two strings s and t, return true if t is an anagram of s, and false otherwise.

 

Example 1:

Input: s = "anagram", t = "nagaram"

Output: true

Example 2:

Input: s = "rat", t = "car"

Output: false

class Solution {
    public boolean isAnagram(String s, String t) {
        
        int[] freq=new int[26];
        if(s.length()!=t.length()) return false;
        for(int i=0;i<s.length();i++)
        {
            freq[s.charAt(i)-'a']++;
            freq[t.charAt(i)-'a']--;
        }

        for(int f:freq)
        {
            if(f!=0)
            {
                return false;
            }
            
        }
        return true;
    }
}
